title: Kendall Jenner is being roasted on Twitter for wearing a latex polo neck to the Emmys
text:
From Cosmopolitan

Kendall Jenner attended the Emmy Awards with her sister Kim wearing a floral strapless gown... and a latex top underneath.

The internet isn't loving the unusual red carpet look.

Kendall Jenner isn't one to play it safe on the red carpet, and we love her for that - but the model might have missed the mark a little bit last night, according to Twitter.

Kendall was at the 2019 Emmy Awards with big sister Kim, as they were both presenting the reality TV award. While Kim stuck to her usual style of black gown - by Vivienne Westwood though, rather than Versace - Kendall mixed it up in a red floral Richard Quinn dress, layered over a black, very shiny polo neck top.

Take a look yourself:





Twitter has been laying into poor Kendall for the look, with many pointing out how, um, sweaty she must be under all that black latex.

Kendall Jenner’s ensemble looks like when you get the sex toys almost hidden in the sofa because your mom dropped by unannounced. #Emmys — Emerson Collins (@ActuallyEmerson) September 23, 2019

Kendall Jenner’s Emmy dress looks like the prom dress every girl wanted at junior prom but lubricated — anne 🐘 (@Styles_Anne_) September 23, 2019

While I don’t agree with the tweet, I have to say..... what the actual efff is Kendall wearing? She looking like she might need to dominate her prom date after the dance and just wore it under her dress to save time. https://t.co/u7vOO62vMh — Allie (@thatgirl__allie) September 23, 2019

Me when I saw Kendall Jenner’s dress: https://t.co/wviwdbuglK — Maryam ✨ (@Reemy_alhamad) September 23, 2019

Kendall Jenner serving Alice in Bondageland with that latex + floral getup #Emmys pic.twitter.com/LxUDdhT8xr — Cooper Jackson (@cooperjackson) September 22, 2019

Not that she cares, I guess. Kendall was working the camera all the way down the red carpet, and we have to give her serious props for being a style chameleon.

This time last week she fooled us all into thinking she'd gone blonde, after she walked the Burberry runway with a new lighter hairdo. But, since she's rocking a slicked-back style in her usual dark colour at the Emmys, we'd guess it was just a wig.

Can't wait to see what look she pulls out of the bag next.
